    eliozo:solutionText """## Solution 

Let us note the following:

$$\\begin{gathered}
(x-y)^{2}+(y-z)^{2}+(z-x)^{2}=x^{2}-2 x y+y^{2}+y^{2}-2 y z+z^{2}+z^{2}-2 x z+x^{2}= \\\\
=2\\left(x^{2}+y^{2}+z^{2}-x y-y z-x z\\right) \\leq 2 \\\\
\\end{gathered}$$

So $(x-y)^{2}+(y-z)^{2}+(z-x)^{2} \\leq 2$. 

