eliozo:SOLN.LV.AMO.2022B.12.4.SUB3 a eliozo:Solution ;
    eliozo:solutionNum 3 ;
    eliozo:solutionText """## Solution 

Subtract $4 \\cos x$ from both sides and get $3 \\sin x=6-4 \\cos x$. 
Raise both sides to the second power to get the following:

$$9 \\sin ^{2} x=36-48 \\cos x+16 \\cos ^{2} x$$

Use the identity $\\sin ^{2} x=1-\\cos ^{2} x$ to rewrite like this:

$$\\begin{gathered}
9\\left(1-\\cos ^{2} x\\right)=36-48 \\cos x+16 \\cos ^{2} x, \\\\
9-9 \\cos ^{2} x=36-48 \\cos x+16 \\cos ^{2} x, \\\\
25 \\cos ^{2} x-48 \\cos x+27=0. 
\\end{gathered}$$

Denote $\\cos x=t$ to get a quadratic equation $25t^2 - 48t + 27 = 0$ and 
discriminant $D=(-48)^{2}-4 \\cdot 25 \\cdot 27=48 \\cdot 48-50 \\cdot 54<0$. 
So the quadratic equation has no roots, and the original equation has no roots either."""@en ;
    eliozo:solutionTextHtml """<h2>Solution</h2>
<p>Subtract $4 \\cos x$ from both sides and get $3 \\sin x=6-4 \\cos x$. 
Raise both sides to the second power to get the following:</p>
<p>$$9 \\sin ^{2} x=36-48 \\cos x+16 \\cos ^{2} x$$

Use the identity $\\sin ^{2} x=1-\\cos ^{2} x$ to rewrite like this:

$$\\begin{gathered}
9\\left(1-\\cos ^{2} x\\right)=36-48 \\cos x+16 \\cos ^{2} x, \\\\
9-9 \\cos ^{2} x=36-48 \\cos x+16 \\cos ^{2} x, \\\\
25 \\cos ^{2} x-48 \\cos x+27=0. 
\\end{gathered}$$

Denote $\\cos x=t$ to get a quadratic equation $25t^2 - 48t + 27 = 0$ and 
